        public boolean implementsMethod(Class<?> targetClass,
                                Method method)
        Description copied from interface: BehaviourMethodProcessor
        Returns true if this processor is able to implement method of targetClass. Implementing the given method does either mean to create an implementation for an abstract method or to override a superclass method.
        Specified by:
        implementsMethod in interface BehaviourMethodProcessor
        Parameters:
        targetClass - The defining class of the respective method.
        method - The method that can be implemented.
        Returns:
        true if this processor is able to create an implementation for method, else false.

      • appliesTo

        public boolean appliesTo(BehaviourClassNode classNode,
                         ExtendedMethod method)
        Description copied from interface: BehaviourMethodProcessor
        Called by the container directly before BehaviourMethodProcessor.process(BehaviourClassNode, ExtendedMethod) is called. Returns true if this processor can be applied to the given method. If BehaviourMethodProcessor.implementsMethod(Class, Method) returns true then BehaviourMethodProcessor.appliesTo(BehaviourClassNode, ExtendedMethod) must also return true for the same method.
        Specified by:
        appliesTo in interface BehaviourMethodProcessor
        Parameters:
        classNode - The owner of the respective method.
        method - The method that should be implemented or transformed.
        Returns:
        true if this processor is able to implement or transform the method, else false.
